==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palmitic
<hw>Pal*mit"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or obtained from, palmitin or palm oil;
<as>as, <ex>palmitic</ex> acid (<chform>C16H32O2</chform>), a white
crystalline substance belonging to the fatty acid series</as>. It is
readily soluble in hot alcohol, and melts to a liquid oil at 62⟦deg⟧
C.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palmitin</ent>⟦br⟧
